926
01:51:09,462 --> 01:51:13,466
When l went out to catch Mohar
Singh, a fierce chase took place.

927
01:51:13,466 --> 01:51:15,434
He was running ahead,
l followed him in my jeep.

928
01:51:18,471 --> 01:51:21,474
His feet got hurt
and came in my hand.

929
01:51:21,474 --> 01:51:23,476
l invited him to sit in my jeep.
l told him ...

930
01:51:23,476 --> 01:51:25,478
You run when road is good
so that l can catch you.

931
01:51:25,478 --> 01:51:28,481
On good road l asked him to
run again.

932
01:51:28,481 --> 01:51:30,483
That road ended in a jungle.

933
01:51:30,483 --> 01:51:32,485
l followed him on foot
in to a swamp.

934
01:51:32,485 --> 01:51:34,487
Mohar Singh jumped out to
other end of swamp.

935
01:51:34,487 --> 01:51:36,489
When l tried to jump
l go caught into the swamp

936
01:51:36,489 --> 01:51:40,493
l was being drawn into the swamp.
l was all-alone.

937
01:51:40,493 --> 01:51:42,495
No animal, no man, not even a bird.

938
01:51:42,495 --> 01:51:45,498
Gradually l was going deep
into the swamp.

939
01:51:45,498 --> 01:51:48,501
What are you looking.
lt's a matter of being afraid.

940
01:51:48,501 --> 01:51:50,503
l didn't know how to save myself.

941
01:51:50,503 --> 01:51:52,505
Suddenly l'd an idea.
l went to a nearby village.

942
01:51:52,505 --> 01:51:54,507
l bought a rope, pulled myself
out and came back here.

943
01:51:54,507 --> 01:51:59,467
You talked too much. Sharafat is
out. Before they come. Let's run.

944
01:52:06,519 --> 01:52:08,521
Take me with you.

945
01:52:08,521 --> 01:52:12,480
lf anybody asks for me -
tell him l'll be in my home.

946
01:52:15,861 --> 01:52:21,534
lf there were few more policemen
like you lndia's prisons will be ...

947
01:52:21,534 --> 01:52:23,536
and all criminals will be free.

948
01:52:23,536 --> 01:52:25,538
Trust me, sir. l had locked up
Sharafat Ali.

949
01:52:25,538 --> 01:52:27,506
You mean they are lying.
- Yes sir.

950
01:52:28,541 --> 01:52:30,543
No sir, we're telling the truth.

951
01:52:30,543 --> 01:52:32,545
Sir, he made us say whatever
he wanted us to say.

952
01:52:32,545 --> 01:52:36,549
He slapped if we said no.
- Pyare always seconded him.

953
01:52:36,549 --> 01:52:38,551
They are obviously lying -
but l don't know why !

954
01:52:38,551 --> 01:52:40,553
Arjun was telling us stories.

955
01:52:40,553 --> 01:52:42,555
l will ...
- You shut up. You speak.

956
01:52:42,555 --> 01:52:45,558
He used cane to make us agree
to whatever he said.

957
01:52:45,558 --> 01:52:47,560
He said he caught
dacoit Mohar Singh.

958
01:52:47,560 --> 01:52:51,519
And said, never say no.

959
01:52:53,566 --> 01:53:00,239
You arrested Mohar Singh. You can't
arrest an ordinary criminal.

960
01:53:00,239 --> 01:53:02,207
How can you arrest Mohar Singh.

961
01:53:03,576 --> 01:53:07,580
l've decided to give you
one last chance.

962
01:53:07,580 --> 01:53:10,583
You know 1/2 Kohinoor diamond is
in England ...

963
01:53:10,583 --> 01:53:12,585
and the other 1/2 has come
back to lndia.

964
01:53:12,585 --> 01:53:15,588
That 1/2 is kept in museum
so people may see it.

965
01:53:15,588 --> 01:53:19,547
l've decided to put you on
duty in that museum.

966
01:53:21,594 --> 01:53:25,553
lf anything goes wrong don't say
that sir, we were not there.

967
01:53:27,600 --> 01:53:34,563
Don't worry, we'll protect the
diamond more than our own life.

968
01:53:41,614 --> 01:53:47,620
This is 1/2 of Kohinoor. Steal it
for me. l'll give your asking price

969
01:53:47,620 --> 01:53:50,623
l read it'll be on public display
after a few days.

970
01:53:50,623 --> 01:53:54,582
lt'll be delivered to you as
soon as it is displayed.

971
01:53:59,632 --> 01:54:03,591
Every time you forget my tea.
- l'll bring it. Why do you pinch.

972
01:54:06,639 --> 01:54:10,598
What do you want?
- What do you have?

973
01:54:17,983 --> 01:54:19,951
All these things.
What should l bring for you?

974
01:54:20,319 --> 01:54:22,321
Bring two plates of everything.

975
01:54:22,321 --> 01:54:25,290
Two plates?
Are more people coming?

976
01:54:25,658 --> 01:54:28,627
We are enough.
- Will two of you eat all that?

977
01:54:29,662 --> 01:54:31,630
Are you eating for
the first time in life?

978
01:54:36,669 --> 01:54:38,671
What is happening?

979
01:54:38,671 --> 01:54:41,640
Perhaps Commissioner is losing
brain along with his hair.

980
01:54:42,675 --> 01:54:44,643
Bring the food l ordered.
- How can l. They ate everything.

981
01:54:50,683 --> 01:54:53,686
There is nothing left in the
kitchen except myself.

982
01:54:53,686 --> 01:54:55,688
Put salt and pepper over me
and eat.

983
01:54:55,688 --> 01:54:58,357
Bring some tea.
- How many dozens?

984
01:54:58,357 --> 01:55:01,360
What's happening? We're two -
we'll take two cups of tea.

985
01:55:01,360 --> 01:55:04,329
l'll see if there is any.
Chances are very remote.

986
01:55:06,699 --> 01:55:08,701
What's happening?
- lt is a challenge.

987
01:55:08,701 --> 01:55:14,333
By assigning security of diamond,
commissioner has given a challenge.

988
01:55:19,712 --> 01:55:22,715
Who ordered the tea.
- You asked me to bring tea.

989
01:55:22,715 --> 01:55:25,718
We don't drink tea.
We drink milk.

990
01:55:25,718 --> 01:55:27,720
Or we take milk pudding.
Go, brink milk pudding.

991
01:55:27,720 --> 01:55:29,688
Why are you bothering.
Better take the tea.

992
01:55:33,726 --> 01:55:36,729
Kohinoor diamond will be brought to
the museum today.

993
01:55:36,729 --> 01:55:39,698
lt will be displaced
to the public tomorrow.

994
01:55:41,734 --> 01:55:43,702
l think we should inspect the
security today.

995
01:56:01,754 --> 01:56:03,756
Here is the milk pudding.

996
01:56:03,756 --> 01:56:07,760
What is this brother.
- l knew you'll say this.

997
01:56:07,760 --> 01:56:11,764
Didn't you say bring milk-pudding.
- We said tea not milk-pudding.

998
01:56:11,764 --> 01:56:15,723
l'll go crazy.
Hey, come here.

999
01:56:16,769 --> 01:56:18,737
Here is your tea.

1000
01:56:19,772 --> 01:56:21,774
Give me Rs.1080.

1001
01:56:21,774 --> 01:56:23,776
What? Rs.1080?

1002
01:56:23,776 --> 01:56:26,745
One cup of tea for Rs.540 !
- Kadir Bhai.

1003
01:56:31,784 --> 01:56:35,743
Why have you been calling me?

1004
01:56:36,455 --> 01:56:38,753
They aren't paying for the
food they ate.

1005
01:56:43,796 --> 01:56:47,800
Are you harassing the kid
with your police uniform?

1006
01:56:47,800 --> 01:56:49,802
Should a call Shyamu.

1007
01:56:49,802 --> 01:56:51,804
Who is Shyamu?
- Your Commissioner, Shyamlal.

1008
01:56:51,804 --> 01:56:54,807
He is my childhood buddy.

1009
01:56:54,807 --> 01:56:58,811
No. Don't phone the Commissioner.
We'll give you the money.

1010
01:56:58,811 --> 01:57:00,813
What is happening?

1011
01:57:00,813 --> 01:57:03,782
Take out the full amount -
and his tip too.

1012
01:57:36,849 --> 01:57:38,851
Who is the security in-charge?

1013
01:57:38,851 --> 01:57:40,853
So What?
l'm the in-charge of this museum.

1014
01:57:40,853 --> 01:57:43,856
Security of diamond is
my responsibility.

1015
01:57:43,856 --> 01:57:45,858
l'll let you in after
investigating your right and left.

1016
01:57:45,858 --> 01:57:50,863
Will you investigate us?
- So What?

1017
01:57:50,863 --> 01:57:54,867
Even thieves wear police uniforms
these days.

1018
01:57:54,867 --> 01:57:56,835
Come in.
- Seems crazy.

1019
01:58:08,881 --> 01:58:10,883
Did you see the arrangement?

1020
01:58:10,883 --> 01:58:14,887
Yes we saw the inside arrangement.
We'll do the outside security.

1021
01:58:14,887 --> 01:58:23,896
You came back again !
What do you want now?

1022
01:58:23,896 --> 01:58:26,899
We've come to inspect security
of the diamond.

1023
01:58:26,899 --> 01:58:28,901
But you just now inspected.
- So what?

1024
01:58:28,901 --> 01:58:31,904
Don't you eat twice a day?
Don't you watch TV or wife twice?

1025
01:58:31,904 --> 01:58:35,908
We may see twice or 1000 times.
Your duty is to show. Show it.

1026
01:58:35,908 --> 01:58:38,877
Okay, come in.
Open the door.

1027
01:58:45,918 --> 01:58:50,923
We've put cameras all around.

1028
01:58:50,923 --> 01:58:55,883
Anyone approach the diamond
will be photographed.

1029
01:58:56,595 --> 01:58:59,894
What's so special about it.
Anybody can dodge the cameras.

1030
01:59:02,601 --> 01:59:08,904
lf anybody touches the showcase -
all alarms will start ringing.

1031
01:59:21,954 --> 01:59:23,922
Did you see the function of alarms.

1032
01:59:24,957 --> 01:59:29,962
Guards, don't worry. This was a
demonstration.

1033
01:59:29,962 --> 01:59:33,921
lnspection of security.
No need to worry.

1034
01:59:42,975 --> 01:59:47,980
Similarly, if anybody picks up the
diamond, the alarms will go on.

1035
01:59:47,980 --> 01:59:51,984
A strong light will be beamed
from here to that cage above.

1036
01:59:51,984 --> 01:59:54,987
And the cage will fall on
the head of the thief.

1037
01:59:54,987 --> 01:59:59,947
Oh, if the cage falls the thief
will become an omelet.

1038
02:00:00,993 --> 02:00:04,997
There is a spot in the diamond.
- So what?

1039
02:00:04,997 --> 02:00:06,999
There is a cut in the diamond.

1040
02:00:06,999 --> 02:00:11,003
Cut in the diamond ! What do you
say? Want to give me heart attack.

1041
02:00:11,003 --> 02:00:13,972
Can't you see cut in the diamond?
- What? What are you talking?

1042
02:00:15,674 --> 02:00:16,971
Can't you see cut in the diamond?

1043
02:00:22,014 --> 02:00:24,983
Put your head above diamond.
- Face and diamond on same level.

1044
02:00:29,021 --> 02:00:31,990
Now l'll slowly move the diamond.

1045
02:00:33,692 --> 02:00:36,028
Relax. A demonstration is in
progress inside.

1046
02:00:36,028 --> 02:00:38,030
Don't move your head.
- Why?

1047
02:00:38,030 --> 02:00:43,035
lf you move, a light beam will
strike the cage above.

1048
02:00:43,035 --> 02:00:45,037
And the cage will come down.

1049
02:00:45,037 --> 02:00:48,040
Then your head will become
a half-fried omelet.

1050
02:00:48,040 --> 02:00:51,999
That's what l told you.
Oh why did you get me caught here.

1051
02:01:03,722 --> 02:01:07,059
What a shameful act. You've
brought shame to police department.

1052
02:01:07,059 --> 02:01:11,063
l sent you for security of diamond.
And you have stolen it.

1053
02:01:11,063 --> 02:01:14,066
Sir, it's false allegation.
We were on duty outside.

1054
02:01:14,066 --> 02:01:16,068
How can we go in to steal it.

1055
02:01:16,068 --> 02:01:19,037
Perhaps you don't know that there
were cameras inside.

1056
02:01:20,072 --> 02:01:24,076
And your idiotic faces have come
in cameras when you were stealing.

1057
02:01:24,076 --> 02:01:26,078
How can this happen, sir.
Why don't you believe us.

1058
02:01:26,078 --> 02:01:28,080
Sir, we have not stolen.

1059
02:01:28,080 --> 02:01:32,084
No, you didn't steal.
Your ghosts came to steal it.

1060
02:01:32,084 --> 02:01:37,089
Until today l've forgiven your
small and big mistakes.

1061
02:01:37,089 --> 02:01:41,093
l covered them. But today's
mistake can't be forgiven.

1062
02:01:41,093 --> 02:01:45,097
You must be punished.
l suspend you.

1063
02:01:45,097 --> 02:01:48,066
Until the diamond is found
you will remain in jail.

1064
02:02:04,116 --> 02:02:07,119
Why did you call so early.
We rushed without taking bath.

1065
02:02:07,119 --> 02:02:11,123
We know the museum is open.
We'll steal and give you diamond.

1066
02:02:11,123 --> 02:02:14,126
lt has already been stolen.
- What?

1067
02:02:14,126 --> 02:02:17,095
Yes. That's why l tell
you to read the newspaper.

1068
02:02:18,130 --> 02:02:20,132
This is Mulayam's picture.

1069
02:02:20,132 --> 02:02:23,101
Pyare Mohan and Arjun Singh.

1070
02:02:25,137 --> 02:02:27,139
Good. They have done our job.

1071
02:02:27,139 --> 02:02:33,100
We fear police but not so much that
we can't get diamond from them.

1072
02:02:39,151 --> 02:02:44,156
Who are you?
- l don't know my own identity.

1073
02:02:44,156 --> 02:02:47,826
Your brother has caused
to much trouble for me.

1074
02:02:47,826 --> 02:02:51,163
Out of fear l can neither sit
at home nor walk on streets.

1075
02:02:51,163 --> 02:02:54,132
So l've taken shelter
in your car.

1076
02:02:55,167 --> 02:02:57,795
l'm sure you'll save me from
your brother. Won't you?

1077
02:03:00,172 --> 02:03:05,804
Good kids are never obstinate.
- Move inside.

1078
02:03:07,179 --> 02:03:10,182
lf my brother comes to know,
he will take you to task.

1079
02:03:10,182 --> 02:03:13,151
We want your brother to know.

1080
02:03:21,860 --> 02:03:24,158
Do you want to get me killed.
Come over here.

1081
02:03:25,197 --> 02:03:28,166
This is not a diamond !
This is a bomb !

1082
02:03:30,202 --> 02:03:33,205
lf you help us sell -
we will get some money.

1083
02:03:33,205 --> 02:03:37,209
Entire Thieves Bazaar will be
sold out but not this diamond.

1084
02:03:37,209 --> 02:03:39,177
Why? What is its value.
- Crores.

1085
02:03:41,213 --> 02:03:47,219
l like this diamond.
Have it cut. l want a ring.

1086
02:03:47,219 --> 02:03:52,224
Have you gone crazy. Where to
sell. Give some idea.

1087
02:03:52,224 --> 02:03:59,231
l know a man. Outwardly he is
an sculptor.

1088
02:03:59,231 --> 02:04:03,235
He buys stolen goods at
international level.

1089
02:04:03,235 --> 02:04:06,204
His name is Zorawar.
Only he can give its price.

1090
02:04:19,251 --> 02:04:23,255
You got your diamond -
give us our money.

1091
02:04:23,255 --> 02:04:25,257
That too in cash and quickly.
We got to move from here.

1092
02:04:25,257 --> 02:04:28,260
l got the diamond.
Where is the heroine?

1093
02:04:28,260 --> 02:04:30,929
Which heroine.
- Heroine. Neha !

1094
02:04:30,929 --> 02:04:34,266
What nonsense. We don't know Neha.
- You mean, Neha isn't with you?

1095
02:04:34,266 --> 02:04:36,234
When we said we don't know -
means we don't know.

1096
02:04:37,936 --> 02:04:40,234
Bring out the baby.

1097
02:04:41,273 --> 02:04:46,278
Brother !
- Brother !

1098
02:04:46,278 --> 02:04:50,282
Did you recognize?
- Face looks familiar.

1099
02:04:50,282 --> 02:04:52,951
She is inspector's sister.

1100
02:04:52,951 --> 02:04:54,919
Brother, save me.

1101
02:04:55,287 --> 02:04:59,246
Look mister. She is neither my
sister, nor l'm her brother.

1102
02:04:59,958 --> 02:05:03,295
You mean this girl isn't
your sister.

1103
02:05:03,295 --> 02:05:05,263
How many times do l have
to say this.

1104
02:05:06,298 --> 02:05:08,633
ls this man your boss?
- Yes

1105
02:05:08,633 --> 02:05:13,305
ls he idiot, blind or deaf?
- Can't hear, understand or see !

1106
02:05:13,305 --> 02:05:17,309
See. Even your brothers don't
care about your modesty.

1107
02:05:17,309 --> 02:05:21,268
Don't blame me.
Do it.

1108
02:05:36,328 --> 02:05:38,296
She is our sister.

1109
02:05:38,997 --> 02:05:45,300
We are bringing Neha.
But don't do anything to Neha.

1110
02:05:57,349 --> 02:06:00,318
Welcome. So you got the
real culprit.

1111
02:06:01,353 --> 02:06:04,356
We knew sir that someday
you'll repent for your action.

1112
02:06:04,356 --> 02:06:06,358
You look very disturbed.

1113
02:06:06,358 --> 02:06:11,318
Neither l got the real culprit -
nor do l repent.

1114
02:06:12,364 --> 02:06:14,366
l've come to tell you
that your sister Seema ...

1115
02:06:14,366 --> 02:06:17,335
What happened to Seema ?
- What has happened to Seema, sir?

1116
02:06:18,370 --> 02:06:20,338
Somebody has kidnapped Seema.
- What ... ?

1117
02:06:22,374 --> 02:06:25,043
Please, sir free me from
here for one day.

1118
02:06:25,043 --> 02:06:27,045
After finding Seema we shall
put ourselves in your hands.

1119
02:06:27,045 --> 02:06:31,383
l'm worried about Seema too.
She is like my own daughter.

1120
02:06:31,383 --> 02:06:34,386
l've notified all police stations
and blocked all roads.

1121
02:06:34,386 --> 02:06:36,388
No harm will be done to Seema.

1122
02:06:36,388 --> 02:06:40,058
But sir, who're the kidnappers -
what do they want?

1123
02:06:40,058 --> 02:06:44,017
What if something happens to Seema.
- Nothing will happen to Seema.

1124
02:06:57,075 --> 02:07:03,378
Hey baldly. Why these dry hiccups?
lf you can't see - open second eye.

1125
02:07:09,421 --> 02:07:12,424
Haven't you seen Ram aur Shyam with
Dilip Kumar in double roll.

1126
02:07:12,424 --> 02:07:15,393
We too saw for first time
in your home.

1127
02:07:38,450 --> 02:07:43,455
Whatever bad has happened in your
life - we were behind that.

1128
02:07:43,455 --> 02:07:47,459
We stole the diamond too.
- Where is the diamond?

1129
02:07:47,459 --> 02:07:49,461
We came out by giving them
the diamond.

1130
02:07:49,461 --> 02:07:52,430
Now they want Neha to
release Seema.

1131
02:07:53,465 --> 02:07:57,469
Did you have any twin brothers?
- No sir.

1132
02:07:57,469 --> 02:07:59,471
Lost in childhood.
- No sir.

1133
02:07:59,471 --> 02:08:02,474
Lost in a fair.
- Absolutely not.

1134
02:08:02,474 --> 02:08:06,478
Where have they come from.
- By grace of God, on public demand

1135
02:08:06,478 --> 02:08:09,447
Your good luck has sent
us to release your sister.

1136
02:08:10,482 --> 02:08:18,490
This is Zorawar's hideout.
We'll come dancing from stairs here

1137
02:08:18,490 --> 02:08:23,450
We'll keep them entertained.
You feed them some intoxicants.

1138
02:08:25,497 --> 02:08:32,460
When shall we enter?
-When we finish singing we'll say ...

1139
02:08:38,510 --> 02:08:40,512
You enter by breaking
this glass window.

1140
02:08:40,512 --> 02:08:45,472
Look. l too will come with you.
What if you run away.

1141
02:08:46,518 --> 02:08:49,521
We are helping and this baldly
uncle is doubting us.

1142
02:08:49,521 --> 02:08:52,524
We won't help you.
Better catch them alone.

1143
02:08:52,524 --> 02:08:54,492
Wait a minute. Don't mind. Sit.

1144
02:08:55,527 --> 02:09:01,159
lf you sing and dance -
l too would like to sing and dance.

1145
02:09:02,200 --> 02:09:05,169
Please take me ...

1146
02:09:08,540 --> 02:09:11,509
Hey brother. Do you remember
when you have to enter.

1147
02:14:35,867 --> 02:14:37,835
They were to enter at this point.
- Haven't come.

1148
02:14:39,871 --> 02:14:41,839
l told you don't trust them.

1149
02:14:42,874 --> 02:14:47,834
Start singing. He's coming.
- Clear up your throat.

1150
02:15:09,233 --> 02:15:11,903
You dance quite well.
Do you think we are stupid.

1151
02:15:11,903 --> 02:15:16,908
You thought we will be down
with tiny bit of drugs.

1152
02:15:16,908 --> 02:15:19,877
This much we normally
eat with our breakfast.

1153
02:15:23,915 --> 02:15:28,875
No one else will dance.
Now only these two will dance.

1154
02:17:36,047 --> 02:17:40,051
You think you're Mughal-e-Azam
and we are Anarkali.

1155
02:17:40,051 --> 02:17:42,053
How much can we dance.

1156
02:17:42,053 --> 02:17:46,012
lf you like we'll come to dance
everyday - morning and evening.

1157
02:17:47,058 --> 02:17:48,059
But let us go now.

1158
02:17:48,059 --> 02:17:50,061
Start dancing else
l'll put the bullet in you.

1159
02:17:50,061 --> 02:17:54,065
lt is wrong. ln olden times dancers
were rewarded with gold and silver...

1160
02:17:54,065 --> 02:17:57,034
You're showing us gun -
so we won't dance.

1161
02:17:59,070 --> 02:18:05,076
You've done enough. Let's go
respectfully soon, else ...

1162
02:18:05,076 --> 02:18:07,078
Otherwise what will you do?

1163
02:18:07,078 --> 02:18:09,046
What will we do ... !
We will dance.

1164
02:18:36,107 --> 02:18:40,111
You did typically like policemen.
Why don't you ever come in time?

1165
02:18:40,111 --> 02:18:45,116
We almost died dance. Had you
delayed more you'd see dead bodies.

1166
02:18:45,116 --> 02:18:48,119
You didn't die.
We came before that.

1167
02:18:48,119 --> 02:18:50,121
Why do you come in end? Why not
early. You always come in end.

1168
02:18:50,121 --> 02:18:55,126
And you're talking as if you
have obliged us by coming.

1169
02:18:55,126 --> 02:18:57,128
Let them go. We aren't going
to spend all life with them.

1170
02:18:57,128 --> 02:19:02,088
We're going. Forgive our
misbehavior. Goodbye.

1171
02:19:10,141 --> 02:19:14,100
Hey! Why are you ogling your eyes.
They are thieves, we're policemen.

1172
02:19:19,817 --> 02:19:23,154
Don't be surprised. He is not your
man. That's over there.

1173
02:19:23,154 --> 02:19:26,157
That day you picked me from the
jeweler's shop.

1174
02:19:26,157 --> 02:19:32,163
And then after the cake in your
home, the food, the dance ...

1175
02:19:32,163 --> 02:19:35,166
Now how can l thank you.

1176
02:19:35,166 --> 02:19:37,168
You were not my brother -
yet you saved my life.

1177
02:19:37,168 --> 02:19:39,170
Why are you embarrassing me.

1178
02:19:39,170 --> 02:19:41,172
ln fact we've nobody in this world.

1179
02:19:41,172 --> 02:19:44,175
That day when you affectionately
called me as your brother ...

1180
02:19:44,175 --> 02:19:47,178
My heart felt music of many strings

1181
02:19:47,178 --> 02:19:50,147
So l felt l must help you.

1182
02:19:50,848 --> 02:19:54,147
ln fact we did good deeds in
confusion. We aren't really good.

1183
02:20:06,197 --> 02:20:08,199
Why is our van going separate
way from others?

1184
02:20:08,199 --> 02:20:11,168
Are we being taken to
some special jail.

1185
02:20:30,221 --> 02:20:32,556
What happened.
Why did you stop the van.

1186
02:20:32,556 --> 02:20:34,892
There are two dead bodies ahead.

1187
02:20:34,892 --> 02:20:40,231
We aren't dead bodies.
We got tired waiting.

1188
02:20:40,231 --> 02:20:46,192
Just give us a ride
to the railway station.

1189
02:20:49,240 --> 02:20:53,199
Doesn't the man standing inside
look like Zorawar.

1190
02:20:54,245 --> 02:20:58,204
He is actually Zorawar. Shameless
man has again cheated the police.

1191
02:20:59,250 --> 02:21:01,218
He is always coming in our way.

1192
02:21:32,283 --> 02:21:35,286
Those who like to be punched -
come to me.

1193
02:21:35,286 --> 02:21:38,255
Those who prefer to be kicked
go to him.

1194
02:22:41,352 --> 02:22:46,312
Did you play with him.
Now come, play with me.

1195
02:24:22,453 --> 02:24:24,455
Do you remember faintly?
- Yes l remember.

1196
02:24:24,455 --> 02:24:27,424
These bastards had made
us dance too much.

1197
02:24:28,459 --> 02:24:31,428
Now we'll be Mughal-e-Azam
- and they'll be Anarkali.

1198
02:25:10,501 --> 02:25:12,503
So everybody has been caught.

1199
02:25:12,503 --> 02:25:15,506
But the real criminal you took army
to catch is missing.

1200
02:25:15,506 --> 02:25:18,175
Sir, we had locked him in the van.

1201
02:25:18,175 --> 02:25:20,177
lf you had locked him in the van
then how did he get out.

1202
02:25:20,177 --> 02:25:23,514
Sir, you got the diamond.
- So should l leave real criminal.

1203
02:25:23,514 --> 02:25:25,516
l don't how did Zorawar vanish.

1204
02:25:25,516 --> 02:25:27,484
Here is Zorawar.

1205
02:25:31,522 --> 02:25:33,490
But where are you people going?

1206
02:25:34,525 --> 02:25:39,530
lndia is a big country.
We'll do our business elsewhere.

1207
02:25:39,530 --> 02:25:41,532
What if l make arrangement
for your livelihood.

1208
02:25:41,532 --> 02:25:44,535
ls he proposing to
take us into the jail?

1209
02:25:44,535 --> 02:25:48,539
God has blessed you with good mind
which you use for stealing.

1210
02:25:48,539 --> 02:25:51,542
Use that brain for serving the
country and the law.

1211
02:25:51,542 --> 02:25:53,510
Will you work for the police?

1212
02:26:00,551 --> 02:26:02,519
Where are you going?

1213
02:26:05,556 --> 02:26:08,559
As a policeman you're
showing hand to policemen.

1214
02:26:08,559 --> 02:26:10,527
Sorry sir, we made mistake.

1215
02:26:13,564 --> 02:26:18,569
These two look familiar.
- Yes. Who are you.

1216
02:26:18,569 --> 02:26:23,574
The van you're moving in
used to be our van.

1217
02:26:23,574 --> 02:26:26,543
And the uniform you are wearing
used to be on our bodies.

1218
02:26:27,578 --> 02:26:30,581
Why are they talking so
insultingly with us.

1219
02:26:30,581 --> 02:26:34,585
Haven't you learnt manners
to talk with your officers?

1220
02:26:34,585 --> 02:26:37,554
lf you talk like this again l'll
make you run naked in the desert.

1221
02:26:38,589 --> 02:26:44,550
And remember. We're very hard.
Never say no to us.

